8 (b) (1) Each person or agency that desires to acquire a painting or object of
9 decorative art for display in or on the premises of any State building, except in a room of
10 the Government House, must receive both prior approval and final acceptance from the
11 Commission.
12 (2) Before giving prior approval or final acceptance in accordance with this
13 subsection, the Commission shall consider:
14 (i) the competence of the artist;
15 (ii) the proposed location of the object; and
16 (iii) the quality, historical significance, and appropriateness of the
17 work.
18 (c) This subtitle does not apply to artwork acquired through the Maryland Public
19 Art Initiative Program established under Title 4, Subtitle 6 of the Economic Development
