21 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
22 (a) (1) A suitable monument of the Ten Commandments shall be placed on the
23 grounds of the Maryland State House.
24 (2) The monument shall contain the following text:
25 “The Ten Commandments
26 I AM the LORD thy God.
27 Thou shalt have no other gods before me.
28 Thou shalt not make to thyself any graven images.
29 Thou shalt not take the Name of the Lord thy God in vain.
30 Remember the Sabbath day, to keep it holy.
31 Honor thy father and thy mother, that thy days may be long upon the land which the
32 Lord thy God giveth thee.
33 Thou shalt not kill.
34 Thou shalt not commit adultery.
35 Thou shalt not steal.

4 HOUSE BILL 1472
1 Thou shalt not bear false witness against thy neighbor.
2 Thou shalt not covet thy neighbor’s house.
3 Thou shalt not covet thy neighbor’s wife, nor anything that is thy neighbor’s.”.
4 (b) The Commission on Artistic Property shall oversee the care and maintenance
5 of the monument of the Ten Commandments after the monument is placed on the grounds
6 of the Maryland State House.
7 (c) This section may be cited as the Ten Commandments Monument Display Act.
8 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
9 (a) There is a Commission on the Ten Commandments Monument.
10 (b) (1) The Commission consists of the following members:
11 (i) two members appointed by the President of the Senate;
12 (ii) two members appointed by the Speaker of the House; and
13 (iii) three members appointed by the Governor.
14 (2) Individuals appointed to the Commission under paragraph (1) of this
15 subsection must have training, expertise, or special interests that will benefit the purposes
16 of the Commission.
17 (c) The Governor shall designate the chair of the Commission.
18 (d) The Division of Historical and Cultural Programs in the Department of
19 Planning shall provide staff for the Commission in consultation with other appropriate
20 agencies, including the State House Trust, the Maryland State Arts Council, and the
21 Department of General Services.
22 (e) A member of the Commission:
23 (1) may not receive compensation as a member of the Commission; but
24 (2) is entitled to reimbursement for expenses under the Standard State
25 Travel Regulations, as provided in the State budget.
26 (f) The Commission shall:
27 (1) as soon as practicable, but not later than December 31, 2025, develop
28 and implement a process for the design, construction, and placement of a monument of the
29 Ten Commandments on the grounds of the Maryland State House by a private entity at no
30 cost to the State;

