1 (2) advise the Governor, the General Assembly, and State agencies on
2 matters relating to the monument;
3 (3) perform other duties necessary to approve the design and site selection
4 for the monument, including arranging for placement of the monument in a location where
5 there are no other monuments; and
6 (4) complete all of its duties by June 30, 2027.
7 (g) In the event that the legality or constitutionality of the monument under this
8 section is challenged in a court of law, the Attorney General may:
9 (1) prepare and present a legal defense of the monument; or
10 (2) request the assistance of a nonprofit legal organization that specializes
11 in First Amendment cases to prepare and present a legal defense of the monument.
12 (h) The placement of the monument may not be construed to mean that the State
13 favors any particular religion or denomination over others.
14 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
15 1, 2025. Section 3 of this Act shall remain effective for a period of 3 years and, at the end of
16 June 30, 2028, Section 3 of this Act, with no further action required by the General
17 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.

